<quantity box="[295,440,1069,1095]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="4.3" valueMax="4.8" valueMin="3.8">3.8â€“4.8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,837,1327]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,336,1107,1133]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">Discussion.</emphasis>
Non-types of 
<taxonomicName box="[506,791,1108,1133]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufobrunneus">
<emphasis box="[506,791,1108,1133]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">Xyleborus rufobrunneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[864,996,1108,1134]" name="Philippines" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">Philippines</collectingCountry>
seen in 
<collectionCode box="[1095,1183,1108,1134]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">BMNH</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[1241,1306,1108,1134]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/djch-y0ck" name="Forest Research Centre" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">FICB</collectionCode>
are almost identical to 
<taxonomicName box="[294,459,1147,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Beaverium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sundaensis">
<emphasis box="[294,459,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">B. sundaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A non-type of 
<taxonomicName box="[652,817,1147,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufonitidus">
<emphasis box="[652,817,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">X. rufonitidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Java (
<collectionCode box="[962,1054,1146,1172]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">BMNH</collectionCode>
) also has a concavity on elytral disc. 
<bibRefCitation author="Browne" box="[217,404,1185,1211]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" refString="Browne, F. G. (1961) The biology of Malayan Scolytidae and Platypodidae. Malayan Forest Records, 22, 255." type="journal article" year="1961">
Browne (
<number box="[332,396,1185,1211]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" value="1961.0">1961</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
placed these species among the &quot; 
<emphasis box="[821,895,1185,1210]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">major</emphasis>
group&quot;, with 
<taxonomicName box="[1067,1264,1185,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudopilifer">
<emphasis box="[1067,1264,1185,1210]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">X. pseudopilifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1280,1375,1185,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Beaverium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latus">
<emphasis box="[1280,1375,1185,1210]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">X. latus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and others, which seem to belong to more than one genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
